Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.10,0:00:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These three have theories about\Nthe murder in the unfinished film.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.94,0:00:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please listen to each of their ideas,\Nand then decide for yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.49,0:00:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the ones who are supposed\Nto know all about mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.74,0:00:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Nakajo Junya. He's the\Nassistant director, on the film crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.58,0:00:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Haba Tomohiro, prop maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.75,0:00:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.79,0:00:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ciao!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.17,0:00:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sawakiguchi Misaki, publicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming all the way over!\NPleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.55,0:00:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.76,0:00:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think this group is all there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.93,0:00:47.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.35,0:00:55.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.70,0:01:03.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.58,0:01:09.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.00,0:01:14.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.38,0:01:19.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:24.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.39,0:01:31.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.82,0:01:39.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.24,0:01:44.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.83,0:01:51.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.09,0:01:58.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.51,0:02:10.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give us a holler later!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.15,0:02:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the Furuoka Deserted\NVillage Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.73,0:02:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.90,0:02:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for having to bring\Nyou into this mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a blast when we started,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but without an ending,\Nit's not cool, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.95,0:02:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, give us a hand, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please share these.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are whiskey bonbons, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they were promotional\Nsamples of a new product.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.27,0:02:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we get started?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:03:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakajo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}, you're on\Nthe film crew, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the shoot very hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had some fun with the performances\Nand production, adlibbing some of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the real chore was getting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took an hour by bus and train.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.96,0:03:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why they chose someplace\Nso far away for the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.08,0:03:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.63,0:03:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone recommended that the place\Nhad an interesting look to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that the Narakubo\Narea had a deserted village,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm surprised they\Nlet you go inside there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same person put in a word for us\Nwith the property manager there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.68,0:03:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that have anything to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. This is\Ninformative. Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.65,0:03:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how is the screenwriter,\NHongo-{\i1}san{\i0}, doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.19,0:03:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't sound very good.\NBut then, you can't really blame her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.95,0:03:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}just not a very\Nwell young woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She's had to stay home\Nfrom school a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't come to the shoot, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she worked so hard on the script\Nthat she couldn't make it there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was Hongo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s script not well-received?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.13,0:04:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one had any problem with it.\NNobody found any fault with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that you secretly wanted to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting at? Everyone accepted\Nthe work that Hongo did!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That goes for me, too, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone hear from Hongo-{\i1}san\N{\i0}who would be playing the villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.53,0:04:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... As far as I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she mentioned something along the lines\Nof wishing good luck to Konosu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:31.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu Yuri
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something she might\Nhave said to {\i1}anyone{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, have you asked all of the actors?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About whether she said\Nanything to any of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, none of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were there any kind of physical or\Npsychological smoke and mirrors?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any other questions?\NOkay, do you want to know what I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.77,0:04:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me, your typical viewer\Ndoesn't care about the shenanigans.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It just has to be thrilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The culprit is you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once called out, the villain breaks\Ndown in tears and gives it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you have that,\Nnobody will complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.41,0:05:14.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The End
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.08,0:05:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming to a head like that would be\Ngreat at paying off Kaito's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our props guy did himself proud\Nin making him die in style.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That scene was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.59,0:05:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that the scene was adlibbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But everyone was so fussy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going on about the rules\Nof a mystery and whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about all the\Nlittle details, it's the drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Play the title straight, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of the Furuoka Deserted Village Murder"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:45.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the Furuoka Deserted Village Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or something like that, because you've\Ngot to put people in the seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Hongo understood that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Nakajo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the way he died, you know\Nwhat it was, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.75,0:05:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito died in a room with no other exits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how did the killer do it?\NThat's the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, so how did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's simple. The window.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. After the villain kills Kaito,\Nhe obviously went out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window... My memory\Nis a bit fuzzy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, do you have the floorplan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.94,0:06:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.03,0:06:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito died right here, stage left wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.79,0:06:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other appearing characters enter\Nhere through the right hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before they do, however,\Nthe door here was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.33,0:06:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so someone went back to get the master key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.59,0:06:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, when they return to\Nstage left wing, Kaito was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.30,0:06:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stage and the hallway backstage\Nwere blocked with junk and obstructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.64,0:07:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the only access to the\Nmurder scene were these two places.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door through which everyone entered,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the window at stage left wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, um, did Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}know these facts?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I just meant, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.83,0:07:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, that is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.74,0:07:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}wrote the script without\Nseeing the condition of the place,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and only went off of the floorplan,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a chance that she\Nconsidered other routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No she didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.17,0:07:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo went to see the location before\Nshe started writing the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,June... no, probably more\Nlike the end of May.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer came and went through\Nthe window. By doing so,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they could pull off shooting Kaito's\Ndeath scene without using the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How 'bout that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about that, he asks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that wouldn't make for\Na very well-crafted mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Tell that to Hongo.\NShe wasn't very up on mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't have any fancy\Ncontrivances set up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say you're right; who was the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, supposing that was the setup,\Nwho does that make the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, once everyone\Narrives at the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.43,0:08:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the outside of the window\Nis shown, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.14,0:08:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at it, there is clearly no trace of\Nanyone having passed by outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.73,0:08:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone had walked through\Nthat overgrown grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there would definitely have\Nbeen some indication.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that wasn't at all what was portrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been impossible\Nfor them to flee out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Hongo forgot to write that in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.70,0:08:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say that, all bets are off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we heard that Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s\Nscript was entirely consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case... hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it! It's summer grass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember I said that Hongo went to\Nscout out the site at the end of May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.30,0:09:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, the summer grass\Nhadn't grown in yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Hongo was convinced\Nthat she could use the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that if we cut that grass\Nwhen we go back to shoot again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and re-shoot the dead body scene,\Nit will all fall into place!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, you see?! How 'bout that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.65,0:09:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, that solves it! The killer\Nfled through the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can pull this off! We're in!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there you have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that count? You can't even\Ncall that a twist, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, from a physical\Nperspective, it {\i1}is {\i0}feasible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.67,0:09:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that what Nakajo-{\i1}san\N{\i0}just said is what Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}intended?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.89,0:09:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it not sit right with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just not entirely convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in other words, it doesn't\Nsit right with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.57,0:09:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are definitely some\Ninconsistencies with what Nakajo said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:09:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?\NWhat? There are inconsistencies?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The utterly simple physical solution
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.99,0:10:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is contradicted by its utterly\Nsimple psychological aspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty convoluted\Nway of saying it, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like someone playing "detective."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.09,0:10:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what exactly do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you put yourself in the killer's shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.05,0:10:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you could never go in through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were to use this window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you run the unavoidable risk of passing\Nthrough someone else's line of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see? Both here and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you walk around outside,\Nyou're sure to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's worse, it's in broad daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure enough. If I were the killer,\NI wouldn't choose that route.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But whether or not Hongo-{\i1}senpai\N{\i0}realized that... we can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. But if we read\Nthe script that Hongo wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would help us figure that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:10:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.09,0:11:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how many detective novels\Nhas everyone read?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking while we\Nwere listening to Nakajo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.10,0:11:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you use the term "crime mystery,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it can be taken to mean\Nlots of different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.90,0:11:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Nakajo's way of thinking\Ncertainly {\i1}is {\i0}novel, in one sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. How about you, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.57,0:11:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a lot. A handful of paperbacks, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.53,0:11:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, about average. Christie, and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The classics, huh? Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't read them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.67,0:11:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all? Ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've read enough to decide that maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't enjoy reading mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't even touched one\Nover the last few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.97,0:11:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh... I wouldn't have expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what about {\i1}you{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.23,0:11:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me? Hm, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.15,0:12:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know. Fuku-{\i1}chan {\i0}fancies\Nhimself as a Sherlockian, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is a Sherlockian?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.53,0:12:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A passionate fan of Sherlock Holmes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}very {\i0}passionate fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.50,0:12:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.37,0:12:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A "Sherlockian" is a little bit\Ndifferent than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.47,0:12:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We rejected Nakajo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.27,0:12:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.81,0:12:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, one other thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.56,0:12:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you find us the script?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.61,0:12:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to know how attentive\NHongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}was, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will go look for one, so until\Nthen, please talk to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prop maker, Haba Tomohiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand you know your mystery stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.97,0:13:08.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shosho {\i0}('Heat's End')\NFor the sunshine easeth,\Nand blue skies begin their withdrawl
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:08.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, if you think of mysteries as being\Na contest between the author and the reader,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.31,0:13:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an amateur like Hongo\Ncomes up a little short.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard that Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}doesn't have\Nmuch experience with mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the books she used to cram with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.32,0:13:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up until she started this film,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.41,0:13:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that she hadn't even seen any\Nmystery manga or movies, let alone novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the Nobuhara translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the latest editions, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was trying to study\Nmysteries by reading Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Which is what\Nmakes her such an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.26,0:13:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.14,0:13:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some odd marks on here. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.89,0:13:58.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.27,0:14:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, look. They're on here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.94,0:14:03.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Casebook of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably just marked the\Nstories she could draw from.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.12,0:14:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.49,0:14:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what do you say we start deducing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this floorplan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it from the town hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please tell us what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To my thinking, this mystery\Nis not all that difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.05,0:14:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I would categorize it as easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.39,0:14:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.34,0:14:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder was not premeditated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, circumstances just happened\Nto fall into place for the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they seized on the chance\Nto commit the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.89,0:14:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it had been planned out,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how would they have lured\NKaito to stage left wing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason Kaito went to the right\Ncorner of the first floor alone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the result of him spontaneously\Npicking up that key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, this is a locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.29,0:14:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the points of escape were blocked,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:14:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the window,\Nwhich was the only route out,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had no footprints left outside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that the culprit who killed Kaito\Ncould not have escaped conventionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer used the master\Nkey to sneak onto the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.18,0:15:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any chance that\Nthey returned it afterward?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.18,0:15:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is neither interesting,\Nnor reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To get to the office where the keys were,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have to pass\Nthrough the front lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was always the danger that they\Nwould be spotted in the lobby
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by any of the other characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So none of the characters could\Nhave safely entered the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.28,0:15:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not just the office\Nthat they couldn't safely enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first-floor hallway down the right side\Nthat leads to the stage left wing itself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is someplace that no one could\Nhave gotten to. That's crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.96,0:15:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They couldn't even get near the locked room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to set the whole\Nthing in motion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the same reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,any chance of the victim himself\Ncreating the locked room is negated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.26,0:15:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other possibilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.39,0:16:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murders committed by mechanical\Nmeans or sleight of hand are out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.65,0:16:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He died after being slashed hard\Nenough to take off his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, this locked-room\Nmystery that Hongo created
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.23,0:16:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is quite difficult to tackle head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.20,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? You're Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.45,0:16:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think this locked-room\Nmurder could be solved?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Golly, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well {\i1}that {\i0}isn't going to do!\NAlthough, who could blame you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the key to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.09,0:16:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the prop master.\NHongo made a point about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said to have a rope that wouldn't\Nbreak, even with a person's weight on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already know how it\Nwill be used, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.19,0:16:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you see? If they couldn't\Nget in from the first floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they could get in from the {\i1}second {\i0}floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu was there on the\Nright second-floor hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:50.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is that while Konosu looks\Nslender, she's in the Mountaineering Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu dangled the rope\Ndown from the second floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:17:01.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Stage left wing\NKaito
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:16:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,climbed down\Nit to stage left wing, killed Kaito,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then escaped back along the same route.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were to give this movie a title,\Nit would be, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I might call it "Unseen Incursion."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let me hear what you guys think now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}ask you for\Nanything aside from the rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, not especially. Hongo was\Na bit capricious, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.77,0:17:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, the amount of blood she\Ncalled for was not nearly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.48,0:17:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to play it smart\Nand get a whole lot of it ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.11,0:17:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not...\NUm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This may not be a big deal,\Nbut have you seen the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I {\i1}haven't {\i0}seen it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it really galls me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His attitude! Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0},\Ndidn't it get to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even made fun of Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:18:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The view that Holmes was intended for\Nbeginning readers is true, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Hongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}was,\Nin fact, a beginner at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.43,0:18:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do we think about Haba's theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's a good one, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The conclusion isn't very thrilling,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.32,0:18:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the fact that Hongo-{\i1}senpai\N{\i0}called for the rope is decisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't find any problem with it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I can't go along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.33,0:18:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like with Nakajo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s theory earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.12,0:18:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something simply feels out of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure why it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't think it was what\NHongo-{\i1}san {\i0}intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you've had enough of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, did I eat all of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They tasted so unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.85,0:18:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was curious if they were\Nsupposed to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I'm fine... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.90,0:18:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Do you think he is correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this were an actual\Nmurder, it might fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it wouldn't work inside the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.50,0:19:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's inconsistent with the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. The window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.59,0:19:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had been left closed for years,\Nand fallen into disrepair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuta gave it a good jolt, and it still didn't\Nwant to open, so it had to have been pretty tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It creaked awfully loudly, too,\Nplus, it opened upward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been impossible for anyone\Nto open quietly while dangling from a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, would Kaito just\Nstand still there in the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the window was being rattled open?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be beyond dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.48,0:19:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you asked Haba if\Nhe had seen the video, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.94,0:19:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo had gone there\Nto scope out the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the window was such\Nan important plot point,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she would have checked to see\Nif it would open or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we all saw the actual\Nfootage they shot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.04,0:19:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Hongo wasn't concerned\Nabout the state of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.13,0:19:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have been so eager to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.26,0:20:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.01,0:20:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.89,0:20:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.69,0:20:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice! Nice! I want one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.57,0:20:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.82,0:20:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, it's shipshape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is pretty detailed, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.74,0:20:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Make sure that there are no\Nfootprints outside the window."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.16,0:20:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure enough, she thought about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where is the next\Nperson... Sawakiguchi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.83,0:20:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ciao!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there, Sawakiguchi-{\i1}san{\i0}. Ciao to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.17,0:20:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, from a publicity standpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuck until this thing has a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making up publicity posters is on hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.93,0:20:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's about time we settled\Nthis matter of the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.31,0:20:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}put herself up as\Na candidate to write the script?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:20:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, she was recommended.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the decision to make a mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was also by majority vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.36,0:21:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the idea to make\Na video in the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.16,0:21:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting off point here, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. I have the meeting minutes.\NIf they're any help, take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.96,0:21:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, why don't you\Nlisten to what I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.67,0:21:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you hear the word "mystery,"\Nwhat do you picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.55,0:21:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Orient Express{\i0}, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a whodunit novel, right?\NWhat a freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.56,0:21:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you look at mysteries\Nat the video rental shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll find {\i1}Friday the 13th{\i0} and {\i1}A Nightmare\Non Elm Street{\i0}, right? Typically.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but those are horror...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.86,0:21:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, indeed you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.07,0:21:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.57,0:21:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it like someone who has\Nno interest at all in the genre.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.16,0:21:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't draw a distinction\Nbetween "mystery" and "horror."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.95,0:21:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.20,0:21:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody could get into the room\Nwhere Kaito died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.29,0:21:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, there obviously\Nhas to be a seventh person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh person?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo was looking for another actor,\Nin addition to the other six.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.30,0:22:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all stop trusting one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.18,0:22:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and once all of their\Nparanoia gets built up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.51,0:22:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the much-anticipated\Nphantom killer appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.10,0:22:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phantom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.23,0:22:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure how many\Nof them get killed off,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.61,0:22:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but other than one lucky couple,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.11,0:22:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they could have probably whacked\Nall the others, I'd guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.07,0:22:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, the couple defeat the phantom,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.53,0:22:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and end with a kiss by dawn's light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.49,0:22:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title would be, let's see,\N"Bloody Beast," maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or whatever. That might be a little cheesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.50,0:22:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you all buy that, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.83,0:22:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, Senpai, what about the locked room?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was the door locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.76,0:22:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it really\Nmatter if it was locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.84,0:22:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A phantom killer has to at least\Nbe able to pass through walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.72,0:22:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.31,0:22:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! A vengeful spirit! Mm-hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:22:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's possible, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.98,0:22:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! You're absolutely wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.85,0:23:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sawakiguchi-{\i1}san{\i0}, your idea is definitely\Nnot what Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}intended!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, for sure. I couldn't tell\Nhow much of it was a joke, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But can you refute it?\NLogically, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.82,0:23:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but logically?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.75,0:23:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.54,0:23:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.42,0:23:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like looking into a kaleidoscope...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleidoscope?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.23,0:23:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.48,0:23:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I liked how bold\NSawakiguchi-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I like it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:23:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.16,0:23:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, it does have its inconsistencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.16,0:23:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.24,0:23:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw how detailed the script was, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.37,0:24:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hongo was planning that kind of\Nhorror twist for the second half,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.12,0:24:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she would have at least\Narranged for the prop for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.54,0:24:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one most necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.38,0:24:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one most necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.59,0:24:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? The one that\NHaba played it smart over?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.01,0:24:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.14,0:24:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo only ordered a very small\Namount of fake blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.35,0:24:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The description in the script backs that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.35,0:24:23.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon helping Kaito-{\i1}kun{\i0} up, there is blood on Sugimura's\Nhand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.10,0:24:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Hongo's intent was not to write a body-count movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.06,0:24:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.19,0:24:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes for a lean horror movie\Nto only have one dead person.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.52,0:24:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a reason for\Neverything, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.16,0:24:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.00,0:24:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, shake it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.33,0:24:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.55,0:24:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turns out we rejected them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.05,0:24:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Step on up! Cheap prices, cheap prices! Step on up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.05,0:24:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's going to become of their video.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.84,0:24:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, mister. Could I please have...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.84,0:24:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they won't be able to finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.18,0:24:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so depressing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.14,0:25:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Summer grass, 'tis all that remains\Nof ancient warriors' dreams."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.27,0:25:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.31,0:25:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.19,0:25:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.19,0:25:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much passion someone puts into it,\Nwithout technical skill, the outcome will be obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.29,0:25:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you spare me time enough\Nfor a cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.93,0:25:37.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.89,0:25:41.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.64,0:25:45.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.64,0:25:50.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.12,0:26:11.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.96,0:26:21.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.39,0:26:28.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.90,0:26:34.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.28,0:26:39.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.99,0:26:45.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.00,0:26:48.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.04,0:26:51.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.75,0:26:55.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.80,0:27:01.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.89,0:27:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Blind Spot to All."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.27,0:27:13.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Blind Spot to All
